	<td width="30%" valign="top">
		<b>Topics and categories (for comedies only)</b>
		<p>This cloud shows most frequent words in movie titles and descriptions.  The data represents all comedies from the New York headend on Saturday Feb 26 2011 starting at or after 8pm.
		<p>Movie categories are shown in blue (comedies can also be tagged with other categories).  The relative sizes of words are based on their frequency. The "Comedy" word has been hidden, since all movies considered are comedies.
		<p> Things to play with:
		<ul>
			<li>Hover over words to see a list of movies whose title or description contains them.</li>
			<li>Uncheck "Groups" - more links will show up</li>
			<li>Focus on a word - all related words and categories will show up</li>
				<ul>
				<li>Note that when hovering over a related word or category the popup list now shows only the movies whose title/description also contain the focused word.</li>
				<li>Click the focused word or click anywhere in the cloud background to unfocus and see the original cloud again</li>
				</ul>
			<li>Remove all category words to emphasize most frequent non-category words.</li>
		</ul>
	<p><a href="http://www.infomous.com/site/mockups/TV/index.html">HOME</a>
